<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-05T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163AM33/60: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-05T15:00:00-05:00">March 5, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>78. Shanghai’s 284, February 19, 5 p.m. Department suggests that, if you
                            have not already done so, you ask the Foreign Office to give serious
                            attention to the substance of Shanghai’s telegram under reference, as
                            further illustrative of the general situation referred to in
                            Department’s 33, February 2, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>